Citations
Date: 0/0/1963
Source: Packtrack to Highway
Author: CHINN
Vol / Page: 42
Edition:
Quote: A Drag Hunt Club was formed. The quarry in this type of hunt was not live game, but a scent was laid down before hand by a sack or sheepskin, impregnated with some strong smell such as anise, being dragged over the course.'
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1976
Source: From the Beginning: chronicles of a county
Author: KERR
Vol / Page: 396
Edition:
Quote: Arthur Barker at Winchester and W Postlethwaite at Raukapuka had packs of beagles too, and the type of hunting indulged in then was the 'drag-hunt' when a bag doused with aniseed was dragged along the course to be followed by the hounds.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1978
Source: From the Toss of a Coin
Author: HAYES
Vol / Page: 90
Edition:
Quote: Jasper Nicols was one-time Master of the Drag Hunt, which was a picnic outing for those who could not ride but still came in buggies to watch.
